#change the_geom to separate columns of long and lat data
x <- str_extract(gf_combined$the_geom,"(?<=\\().*(?=\\))")
x <- unlist(strsplit(x," "))
#Extract long+lat data
odd <- seq(1,201,2)
even <- seq(2,202,2)
long <- c()
lat <- c()

for (i in 1:101){
  long[i] <- x[odd[i]]
  lat[i] <- x[even[i]]
}
gf_combined$long <- as.numeric(long)
gf_combined$lat <- as.numeric(lat)

merged_plot <- merged_combined %>% mutate(across(where(is.numeric), ~ round(., 3))) %>% select(borough,"Economic Need Index",long,lat)
names(merged_plot)[2] <- "ENI"
merged_plot$ENI <- merged_plot$ENI*100
merged_plot <- na.omit(merged_plot)

nyc.map <- get_map(location = "Bronx, New York City", zoom = 10, maptype = "roadmap")
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=Bronx,%20New%20York%20City&zoom=10&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=roadmap&language=en-EN&key=xxx
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=Bronx,+New+York+City&key=xxx
ggmap(nyc.map, extend = "device", darken = 0.3) +
  stat_density2d(aes(x = long, y = lat, fill = ..level.., alpha = ..level..),
                 data = merged_plot, geom = "polygon", bins = 10) +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "red", mid = "blue", high = "firebrick2", midpoint = 80,
                       guide = guide_colorbar(title = "Level")) +
  theme_void()+
  geom_point(aes(x=long,y=lat,color=borough),data = gf_combined,size=0.7)
